      "section_id": "para_35",
      "heading": "1.   (1)   This Act may be cited as the Counterfeit Act 1957.",
      "content": "1.   (1)   This Act may be cited as the Counterfeit Act 1957.",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "heading"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_36",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "(2)  This Act shall apply throughout Malaysia.",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_37",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "Interpretation",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_38",
      "heading": "2.   In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires—",
      "content": "2.   In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires—",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "heading"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_39",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "“counterfeit”  has  the  meaning  assigned  to  it  by  the  Penal  Code",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_40",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "[Act 574];",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_41",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "“current  coin”  means  any  coin  made  by  law  a  legal  tender  in",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_42",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "Malaysia.",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_43",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "Coin suspected to be diminished or counterfeit may be cut by any \nperson to whom it is tendered",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_44",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "3.   (1)   Where  any  coin  is  tendered  as  current  coin  to  any  person \nwho suspects the same to be diminished otherwise than by reasonable \nwear or to be counterfeit, such person may cut, break, bend or deface \nsuch coin.",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_45",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "6                                   Laws of Malaysia                              ACT 429",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_46",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "(2)",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_47",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "If  any  coin  so  cut,  broken,  bent  or  defaced  appears  to  be \ndiminished  otherwise  than  by  reasonable  wear,  or  to  be  counterfeit, \nthe person tendering the same shall bear the loss thereof.",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_48",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "If the same is of due weight and appears to be lawful coin, the \n  (3) \nperson cutting, breaking, bending or defacing the same shall receive \nthe same at its face value.",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_49",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "If any dispute arises whether the coin so cut, broken, bent or \n  (4) \ndefaced  is  diminished  in  manner  aforesaid  or  counterfeit,  it  may  be \nheard and finally determined in a summary manner by a Magistrate’s \nCourt which is hereby empowered to examine upon oath as well the \nparties as any other person in order to the decision of the dispute.",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_50",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "(5)  Every public officer, to whom in the performance of his duties \nthere  is  tendered  in  payment  of  any  part  of  the  revenue  of  any \nGovernment in Malaysia or presented for inspection or otherwise any \ncoin which appears to be a counterfeit of current coin or to have been \nunlawfully diminished, shall cut, break or deface or cause to be cut, \nbroken or defaced every such coin.",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_51",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "7",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
